      "note": "Lit., \"they have given [it] the lie\": an allusion to the prediction of the Last Hour and the Day of Resurrection. The use of the past tense indicates conscious intent or determination (cf. surah 2, note 6). For my rendering of sihr as \"delusion\", see surah 74, note 12."
